9. Innovation Opportunities
Cortex-powered "Why did spend spike?" — When an anomaly is detected, automatically run CORTEX.COMPLETE grounded on the contributing query hashes, warehouse events, and config changes from that time window. Present a natural-language root cause hypothesis, not just "anomaly detected."

Predictive contract breach alerting — Using ML.FORECAST on daily credit consumption, alert 14 days before projected contract exhaustion. Include confidence intervals and a "what-if" slider for planned workload additions.

Self-healing recommendations with cost/benefit — "Warehouse X queued for 45 min yesterday. Upsizing to L would cost ~X/day but save ~Y minutes of developer wait time (at Z/hour loaded cost). Approve?" with a one-click SQL generator.

Query regression fingerprinting — Track p95 runtime per query hash over time. When a query regresses >2σ after a schema change or new data load, automatically correlate with the change event and surface it in Control Room before users complain.

Cost attribution to business outcomes — Connect warehouse spend to the pipelines/reports they serve. "This 4k/month warehouse exists to refresh the daily revenue report that 3 executives view. Cost per consumer: 1,333/month." Let leadership decide if that's worth it.

Automated governance drift detection — Monitor for: new tables without masking policies, new roles with ACCOUNTADMIN grants, warehouses created without resource monitors, users without MFA after 7 days. Surface as a "governance debt" score alongside the platform score.

Incident correlation timeline — Unified timeline view: config changes, alert fires, query failures, task failures, spend spikes — all on one axis. Click any event to see what else happened ±30 minutes. This is what Datadog does well and what this dashboard completely lacks.

